Color of Night is a 1994 American erotic mystery thriller film produced by Cinergi Pictures and released in the United States by Hollywood Pictures .
Directed by Richard Rush , the film stars Bruce Willis and Jane March .
The cast also features Ruben Blades , Lesley Ann Warren , Brad Dourif , Lance Henriksen , Kevin J. O'Connor and Scott Bakula .
It is one of two well-known works by director Rush , the other being The Stunt Man 14 years before .
Color of Night flopped at the box office and won a Golden Raspberry Award as the worst film of 1994 .
Nonetheless , it became one of the 20 most-rented films in the United States home video market in 1995 .
Maxim magazine also singled the film out as having the Best Sex Scene in film history .